tarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Alejandro Abdelnur","active":true,"timeZone":"Europe/Madrid"},"body":"OK, but his does not address the issue of JobClient creation using a custom 'mapred.job.tracker' (and not hadoop site.xml files around)","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=tucu00","name":"tucu00","key":"tucu00","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Alejandro Abdelnur","active":true,"timeZone":"Europe/Madrid"},"created":"2012-03-22T15:49:06.237+0000","updated":"2012-03-22T15:49:06.237+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12547325/comment/13235672","id":"13235672","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=mahadev","name":"mahadev","key":"mahadev","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Mahadev konar","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"Actually am not sure if thats true. Have you tried it? ","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=mahadev","name":"mahadev","key":"mahadev","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Mahadev konar","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2012-03-22T15:56:29.717+0000","updated":"2012-03-22T15:56:29.717+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12547325/comment/13235734","id":"13235734","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=tucu00","name":"tucu00","key":"tucu00","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Alejandro Abdelnur","active":true,"timeZone":"Europe/Madrid"},"body":"ConfigUtil has:\n\n   Configuration.addDeprecation(\"mapred.job.tracker\",\n      new String[] {JTConfig.RM_ADDRESS});\n\nIt seems we should add:\n\n   Configuration.addDeprecation(JTConfig.JT_IPC_ADDRESS,\n      new String[] {YarnConfiguration.RM_ADDRESS});\n\nAnd also we may need to change Configuration logic to do a transitive closure of deprecated keys.\n\nThis is becoming a mess.\n\nThoughts?\n","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=tucu00","name":"tucu00","key":"tucu00","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Alejandro Abdelnur","active":true,"timeZone":"Europe/Madrid"},"created":"2012-03-22T17:12:05.008+0000","updated":"2012-03-22T17:12:05.008+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12547325/comment/13430697","id":"13430697","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=kamrul","name":"kamrul","key":"kamrul","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Mohammad Kamrul Islam","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"Is there any update on this?\n","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=kamrul","name":"kamrul","key":"kamrul","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Mohammad Kamrul Islam","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"created":"2012-08-07T22:47:50.009+0000","updated":"2012-08-07T22:47:50.009+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12547325/comment/13432104","id":"13432104","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jlowe","name":"jlowe","key":"jlowe","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Jason Lowe","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Chicago"},"body":"I think this isn't as straightforward as adding a deprecation, primarily because this is a deprecation across configuration files.  yarn-default.xml and yarn-site.xml load before mapred-default.xml and mapred-site.xml.  If yarn-site.xml sets yarn.resourcemanager.address to an appropriate value, it will be later smashed to \"local\" by mapred-default.xml if we tie yarn.resourcemanager.address to mapreduce.jobtracker.address.\n\nIn addition I think we'd need to update Configuration deprecation support to handle multiple deprecated values mapped to the same new key (i.e.: mapred.job.tracker *and* mapreduce.jobtracker.address would both need to map to yarn.resourcemanager.address).  I don't think the deprecation code currently handles a many-to-one mapping, although oddly it appears to support one-to-many.\n\nBottom line is that this change smells pretty risky, certainly not as easy as a one-line Configuration.addDeprecation() call.  Would it make more sense from a risk-mitigation standpoint to have Oozie set both mapred.job.tracker and yarn.resourcemanager.address so it can work with both 1.x and 2.x?","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jlowe","name":"jlowe","key":"jlowe","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Jason Lowe","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Chicago"},"created":"2012-08-09T20:07:10.245+0000","updated":"2012-08-09T20:07:10.245+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12547325/comment/13432110","id":"13432110","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=tucu00","name":"tucu00","key":"tucu00","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Alejandro Abdelnur","active":true,"timeZone":"Europe/Madrid"},"body":"@jason, what you suggest is exactly what Oozie is currently doing. Agree the deprecation thingy is not that simple. Still the problem impacts apps in general outside of Oozie that set 'mapred.*' values.\n","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=tucu00","name":"tucu00","key":"tucu00","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Alejandro Abdelnur","active":true,"timeZone":"Europe/Madrid"},"created":"2012-08-09T20:16:20.913+0000","updated":"2012-08-09T20:16:20.913+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12547325/comment/13432203","id":"13432203","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=acmurthy","name":"acmurthy","key":"acmurthy","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Arun C Murthy","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"I'm confused. I